9.1 General
This document specifies three implementation levels.
System software products that meet the corresponding implementation level should provide input and output functions for all characters within the scope of the corresponding implementation level.
9.2 Implementation Level 1
Implementation level 1 supports the CJK unified Chinese characters (ie, 0x82358F33 to 0x82359636) and CJK unified Chinese character extensions (ie, 0x8139EE39 to 0x82358738) of the single-byte encoding part, the double-byte encoding part, and the four-byte lower encoding part of this document.
Any product to which this document applies shall meet the requirements of Implementation Level 1.
Note: According to the software application requirements, implementation level 1 can also select any one or more non-Chinese scripts listed in Table 3.
9.3 Implementation Level 2
Implementation level 2 includes implementation level 1.
In addition, implementation level 2 also supports the coded Chinese characters in the &quot;General Standard Chinese Character Table&quot; that are not included in implementation level 1.
The code positions and glyphs of the Chinese characters included in the &quot;General Standard Chinese Character Table&quot; are shown in the appendix.
System software and supporting software should meet the requirements of implementation level 2.
Note: System software and document support software include but are not limited to operating systems, database management systems, and middleware (for information on software product classification, see GB/T 36475).
9.4 Implementation Level 3
Implementation level 3 includes implementation level 2.
In addition, implementation level 3 also supports all Chinese characters specified in this document and the Kanghei radicals in Table 3.
Products used for government services and public services should meet the requirements of implementation level 3.
Note: Government services and public service industries include but are not limited to railway transport, road transport, water transport, aviation transport, multimodal transport and transport agency, postal service, monetary and financial services, insurance, land, management, health, national institutions, social security, etc. (For information on industry classification, see GB/T 4754).
