Top 10 countries for overseas students seeking employment in China in 2022 Source: 2022 China Returnees Employment Survey Report
China News Service, Beijing, February 11 (Men Rui) The recently released &quot;2022 China Returnees Employment Survey Report&quot; (hereinafter referred to as the &quot;Report&quot;) shows that the number of new overseas students in 2022 increased by 8.6% year-on-year, the number of overseas students returning to China to find jobs reached a new high, and the demand of Chinese companies for overseas talents also showed an upward trend.
The report pointed out that since 2020, the number of returnees seeking employment in China has increased significantly, and the number of fresh international students returning to China to seek employment has increased.
