Save half the cost or more?
Henan Province standardizes and integrates prices of oral implant medical services
CCTV News: Dental implants are an ideal choice for many patients with missing teeth, but the price of tens of thousands of yuan per implant has always been a prohibitive price for many patients.
Since the beginning of this year, with the accelerated implementation of centralized procurement of dental implants, various regions have also put price reduction of dental implants on the agenda.
Starting from February 10, the full-process price control target for a single conventional dental implant medical service in Henan Province is 4,300 yuan, and the full-process cost of a single conventional implant is no more than 97% of the control target.
Dental implants refer to a method of restoring missing teeth that uses a lower structure implanted in bone tissue to support and retain the upper dental restoration.
The reporter learned from the First Affiliated Hospital of Zhengzhou University that, taking a single conventional implant as an example, the price from implantation to final restoration is about 16,000 to 17,000 yuan.
Patient He Ying: After the new policy was introduced, the doctor told me that a case like mine would cost around 8,000 yuan, less than 10,000 yuan, so I can basically save half of that.
On the basis of the current items, Henan Province has also integrated and determined 15 oral implant medical service price items such as &quot;implant insertion fee (single)&quot;, and unified the prices and medical insurance payment categories of provincial public medical institutions, and canceled or adjusted 20 medical service price items such as dental implant implantation.
Li Yunjie, director of the Medical Price and Tendering and Procurement Department of the Zhengzhou Medical Insurance Bureau: There are four main beneficiaries. One is medical insurance, which will see less spending; the pressure on hospitals will be reduced, and the number of patients will increase appropriately; suppliers will gain a market; and we patients are the ones who benefit the most, as the cost of implanting a tooth may be halved or even more.
