“New variables” emerge in China’s e-commerce industry. How can we achieve “content is king” when selling products?
-China News Service
China News Service, February 11, titled: &quot;New variables&quot; emerge in China&#39;s e-commerce industry, how to achieve &quot;content is king&quot; in selling products?
Xia Bin, China News Service reporter
“We entered the e-commerce market relatively late, but we realized from the beginning that content is very important if we want to stand out from thousands of stores.
Fangfang, a post-90s girl from Guangdong, now runs a nourishing food store on Douyin e-commerce, making an offline store with more than 30 years of history flourish online.
Imitating the tone of old Hong Kong movies and accompanied by classic Cantonese songs, open the Douyin account of @芳芳壹食, and the exquisite videos will be refreshing.
At the Douyin e-commerce &quot;Looking for Companions and Sharing High-quality Content&quot; event held recently, Fangfang spoke as a representative of high-quality creators and introduced her daily creative experiences and insights.
She said at the event: &quot;The carefully polished video has attracted a lot of attention from netizens. Many people are interested in my family&#39;s ingredients and want to cook delicious food together, so the sales have opened up all of a sudden.
”
Fangfang has made more people fall in love with the &quot;taste of old Guangzhou&quot; through her soup-making videos. She has sold up to 300,000 pieces of nutritious ingredients in one live broadcast, saving her family&#39;s old store which was on the verge of bankruptcy.
&quot;No content, no e-commerce.&quot; With the continuous development of short videos and live streaming e-commerce, people&#39;s requirements and standards for e-commerce content are entering a new stage.
In the early stages of live streaming e-commerce, live streaming rooms often used low prices and discounts to attract users, and price advantage seemed to be the only selling point at the time.
In recent years, there have been phenomenal big Vs such as Liu Genghong and Oriental Selection, as well as many unknown experts and businesses that have emerged in vertical segments. They have improved their long-term operating efficiency by continuously creating high-quality content that is in line with their brand tone.
Gao Yaxuan, head of operations for celebrity authors on Douyin e-commerce, said that in the past year, 6.27 million creators monetized their content through Douyin e-commerce, with their content creation volume increasing by 252% and total transaction volume more than doubling.
“Behind these figures, we can feel a thriving and vibrant author ecosystem.
Gao Yaxuan said.
The Communication Innovation and Future Media Experimental Platform of Beijing Normal University previously released the &quot;E-commerce Industry Content Ecological Health Index (ECHI) Report&quot;, which analyzed the importance of the &quot;new variable&quot; in the current e-commerce industry - high-quality content from a data dimension, and used the index to evaluate the content ecology of 27 mainstream e-commerce platforms in China.
According to the e-commerce industry content ecological health index ranking in the above report, Douyin E-commerce, Kuaishou, Taobao, Pinduoduo, and JD.com ranked in the top five.
The report believes that the content ecology of the e-commerce industry is a comprehensive concept that integrates e-commerce and content, but not all content can be integrated with e-commerce. Good PGC (professionally produced content) and UGC (user-generated content) are high-quality carriers for integration with e-commerce. The higher the value of the content platform, the richer the consumption and promotion scenarios will be, the higher the possibility of e-commerce implantation will be, and the stronger the commercial value will be. The proportion of e-commerce content production and content consumption that is gradually integrated and distributed in the public and private spheres will also be higher.
At the scene, Yu Guoming, professor of the School of Journalism and Communication of Beijing Normal University and chairman of the China Media Economics and Management Professional Committee, analyzed and interpreted the report.
He said that in terms of content value, the current e-commerce industry has transitioned from the &quot;consumer accessibility&quot; stage to the &quot;consumer quality&quot; stage, and high-quality, professional and differentiated content is the &quot;hard currency&quot; of the e-commerce industry.
At the same time, content has become the foundation and driving force for the new stage of e-commerce development. PGC content such as knowledge payment, professional knowledge, KOL (key opinion leaders), etc. has begun to become standard in e-commerce live broadcasts.
Looking forward to the future development of the e-commerce industry, Yu Guoming put forward two suggestions.
One is to promote the overall improvement of the health and quality of the e-commerce content ecosystem from the perspective of improving the content structure, create positive content creation and management standards, and achieve a healthy system index and dynamic balance in the e-commerce industry&#39;s content ecosystem.
The other is to look at the external ecology and achieve the healthy development of the content e-commerce industry and the value synergy and co-creation of the external environment.
&quot;In the future, the e-commerce industry will need more support from data and artificial intelligence to form predictions on the stability of future development. In addition, it will provide merchants with a more standardized and healthy growth space, realize the value synergy of enterprises, users, products and services in the e-commerce industry, and jointly create a healthy content ecosystem.
&quot;(over)
