On February 10, the China Securities Regulatory Commission announced that the &quot;Fund E-Account&quot; APP was launched on various mobile application stores and started public trial operation.
According to reports, &quot;Fund E Account&quot; provides individual investors with a &quot;one-stop&quot; query service for public fund accounts and share information, aiming to solve industry service pain points such as small and medium-sized investors forgetting their accounts and cumbersome queries.
According to Wind data, as of the end of 2022, there were 156 public fund managers in China, with a total fund size of approximately 26 trillion yuan; there were 167 public fund share registration institutions and 411 public fund sales institutions.
The account systems of various share registration institutions are independent of each other, and there is a lack of a unified inquiry channel in the industry.
Industry insiders said that at the end of 2021, there were more than 720 million fund investors in my country, which means that half of the people in the country had invested in fund products.
Previously, investors needed to check purchase status through different sales agencies, but through the &quot;Fund E Account&quot;, they can check the purchase status of all sales channels, and the status of fund holdings is clear at a glance.
What is the “Fund E Account” APP?
According to relevant documents, the &quot;Fund E-Account&quot; APP is a mobile phone portal application for the public fund industry developed and constructed by China Securities Depository and Clearing Corporation with the approval of the China Securities Regulatory Commission. It can provide investors with a one-stop query on the over-the-counter share holdings of public fund products across the market.
Investors can use &quot;Fund E Account&quot; to conveniently and quickly understand their holdings of over-the-counter shares of public fund products under various fund managers purchased through various sales channels across the market, thereby comprehensively improving query efficiency.
Specifically, the information that investors can query through &quot;Fund E Account&quot; includes: fund account information opened with public fund managers in the entire market, trading account information opened with public fund sales institutions, and over-the-counter share holdings of products including publicly offered securities investment funds and collective asset management plans established and managed by securities companies with the number of investors not being limited to 200.
Liu Yiqian, business manager of Shanghai Securities Fund Evaluation and Research Center, told the Economic Observer reporter that investors can use the &quot;Fund E Account&quot; App to obtain one-stop information on all their over-the-counter public fund holdings, helping them to retrieve &quot;forgotten assets&quot;. More importantly, it enables customers to collect full account information on comprehensive fund investment conditions, helping customers to grasp their own investment situation more timely, accurately and completely, so as to better optimize their fund portfolio allocation and better plan their own financial arrangements.
How to register and use?
The reporter noticed that at present, the &quot;Fund E Account&quot; APP has been available on mobile application stores such as Huawei, Apple, Xiaomi, OPPO, and vivo, but the APP is still in the public trial operation stage. Registration requires filling in an invitation code, and investors can contact the fund manager of the fund they hold to obtain it.
A customer service representative of a medium-to-large public offering fund in Shanghai provided a 6-digit invitation code to the Economic Observer reporter and told the reporter, &quot;During the trial operation phase of the APP, China Securities Depository and Clearing Corporation Limited provides a certain number of invitation codes to each fund manager. We will provide them to investors who call to obtain them.
After the trial run is over, the invitation code will no longer be required when user registration is allowed.
”
The reporter registered an account and completed the query according to the download and usage instructions of the &quot;Fund E Account&quot; published on the official website of the China Securities Regulatory Commission. The whole process took only a few minutes and was mainly divided into four steps: user registration, real-name authentication, fund account binding, and public fund query.
After passing the real-name authentication step, click the &quot;Asset&quot; fund binding button, and all the fund products purchased by the reporter through various fund sales platforms will be presented in the binding option list (accounts can be bound). After completing the binding, you can intuitively see the total assets of the invested funds and start using the query function.
It is worth noting that the &quot;Fund E Account&quot; only provides inquiry services for investors and cannot be used for subscription, redemption, and trading.
The data date displayed in &quot;Fund E Account&quot; is generally three trading days before the date the user makes an inquiry (T day).
For example, if you open the &quot;Fund E Account&quot; on February 10, the total assets, fund shares, and fund net value displayed on the asset page correspond to the date three trading days before that date, which is February 7.
