What exactly was the &#39;object&#39; shot down over Alaska?
Confusing and full of speculation
The U.S. military once again used its most advanced stealth jet fighter, the F-22, to shoot down an unidentified object flying over Alaska on Friday afternoon (February 10).
The downing took place ten miles off the coast of Alaska.
This is the second time the US military has shot down a flying object in less than a week.
A spy balloon from China was shot down near the coast of South Carolina last Saturday after drifting in U.S. airspace for several days.
The Pentagon said the second object shot down first entered U.S. airspace on Thursday evening and was tracked by the U.S. military as it moved over northeastern Alaska at an altitude of 12,000 meters (40,000 feet). It was about the size of a small car and much smaller than the Chinese spy balloon that was shot down earlier.
The Pentagon also believes that there is no indication that the object is maneuverable.
John Kirby, the White House National Security Council&#39;s strategic communications coordinator, said Friday that while the exact appearance of the high-flying object was unclear, it &quot;poses a legitimate threat to the safety of civilian aircraft.&quot;
Kobe said the object was different from the spy balloon found in the United States and did not have a &quot;payload&quot; hanging on it.
&quot;Calling it an &#39;object&#39; is the best description we can give at this point,&quot; Bryant said.
President Biden listened to the Pentagon&#39;s advice before ordering the object to be shot down, and he made the decision &quot;out of an abundance of caution,&quot; Bryant added.
The official U.S. description of this object can be roughly summarized as: it is about the size of a car, has no joystick, no suspension device, and flies at an altitude of about 10,000 meters.
But the information still cannot answer basic questions, such as what exactly the object is, which country it belongs to, and what mission it is carrying out.
Currently, many analyses and speculations on the Internet believe that this may be another Chinese balloon.
It may be that it came from China, just like the spy balloon that invaded US airspace and the Chinese balloon floating over Latin America, and they are performing some kind of mission in different locations.
