This book is not so much a collection of short stories as it is a collection of fragments about love in life.
The writing style of this book is extremely plain, as plain as boiled water. The choice of words and sentences pursues simplicity to the extreme, and the plot is as quiet and plain as a street in a summer afternoon.
Each short story is a snapshot of a small period of time in ordinary life, with no beginning and no end.
Finally, they were collected together and titled &quot;What We Talk About When We Talk About Love&quot;.
I think this collection of novels, and its title, is like a kind of performance art. What the author wants to express is that love is not only the joys and sorrows on the stage, the everlasting love in urban legends, nor is it just the infatuation between you and me. Love is not only the above and should not be represented by the above. Love is also a life as plain as water, boring day after day, helplessness in life, escape from reality, and confusion about the future.
When reading this book, you may recall the quarreling couples around you, the boring marriages of people you know, and the unhappy relationships.
This is exactly why I don&#39;t recommend reading it. From an aesthetic point of view, the writing style and plot of this book are dull. Unless your life is full of turmoil or as sweet as living in a candy castle, you will feel indifferent and bored when reading it.
