I appreciate you and want you to know!
The first factor that determines a person&#39;s job satisfaction is not the salary, but whether he or she is given enough attention and appreciation at work.
According to Maslow&#39;s hierarchy of needs theory, after people&#39;s basic survival needs are met, the most urgent thing is the satisfaction of psychological needs - the desire to be understood, affirmed, and appreciated.
Indeed, for most Chinese people, it is difficult to express their love for you. Even if they have love, gratitude and admiration, they keep it in their hearts and will not say it out loud.
In this book, the author explains five languages of appreciation: words of affirmation, quality time, acts of service, thoughtful gifts, and physical touch.
I think what’s important is not that you know what the five languages of appreciation are, but that you can use these five languages from the bottom of your heart anytime and anywhere to appreciate and be grateful to those around you, whether they are family, friends or colleagues.
In fact, the closer the people are to us, the more they need appreciation and gratitude, so that our lives will become better.
By learning to appreciate, companies can retain talent to a certain extent and reduce the resignation rate.
Thanks to the translator for bringing us wonderful foreign ideas and world.
